# Trivy CVE ignore list
#
# Each entry MUST include:
#   reason   - why this CVE is being suppressed (false positive, no fix
#              available upstream, not exploitable in our config, etc.)
#   owner    - who accepted the risk
#   review   - YYYY-MM-DD by which we re-evaluate / try to remove this entry
#
# A scheduled `Trivy Re-scan` workflow runs the same image scan WITHOUT this
# file weekly, so suppressed CVEs surface in the workflow summary even if
# they're still ignored by the gating scan in `docker-publish.yml`.
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line, prefix with `# ` for comments.
# https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#by-finding-ids

